 Nigeria has recorded 675 new cases of the Coronavirus According to a tweet from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Monday night, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Nigeria is now 20,919, with 7,109  persons discharged. The breakdown of figures recorded according to states is as follows: Lagos-288 Oyo-76 Rivers-56 Delta-31 Ebonyi-30 Gombe-28 Ondo-20 Kaduna-20 Kwara-20 Ogun-17 FCT-16 Edo-13 Abia-10 Nasarawa-9 Imo-9 Bayelsa-8 Borno-8 Katsina-8 Sokoto-3 Bauchi-3 Plateau-2 525 persons have so far lost their lives in Nigeria due to Coronavirus, the tweet said.  675 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-288Oyo-76Rivers-56Delta-31Ebonyi-30Gombe-28Ondo-20Kaduna-20Kwara-20Ogun-17FCT-16Edo-13Abia-10Nasarawa-9Imo-9Bayelsa-8Borno-8Katsina-8Sokoto-3Bauchi-3Plateau-2 20,919 confirmed7,109 discharged525 deaths pic.twitter.com/7nAWZGBiYY — NCDC (@NCDCgov) June 22, 2020  